description:
&lt;p&gt;In Pembrokeshire we are committed to continuous improvement of stroke services across the pathway. An opportunity has arisen for a Specialist Physiotherapist (Stroke) post within Withybush General Hospital who will be responsible for delivering specialist quality care in the acute ward setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have acute stroke and stroke rehabilitation skills and work within a highly experienced Stroke MDT. The post holder will be responsible for delivering excellent stroke care, contributing to service development projects and meeting stroke national audit targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexibility will be required to work across the Stroke pathway as services develop. Focus will be on patients remaining central to decision making around their own care and encourage self-management as appropriate. Excellent clinical reasoning and therapy handling skills are a prerequisite for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will be able to demonstrate leadership skills and contribute to the day to day co-ordination of caseload and deputise for senior clinicians, in addition to flexibly supporting wider rehabilitation patient groups if required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our teams are positive, forward thinking and dynamic. The University Health Board proactively supports training and development both as part of internal and external CPD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hywel Dda is situated in a beautiful part of West Wales with award winning beaches and National Parks. The area has a rich heritage and history. There are also vibrant social communities that will help you find a better work life balance. It is a part of the UK that attracts many thousands of tourists every year. Why not make a positive professional move and also live in a place that other people only get to visit on holidays. We’d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time or part time hours considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 24.11.2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
